"children":[
"Heparin-Induced Thrombocytopenia and Thrombosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s23_1",
"title":{
"__html":"Diagnosis"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"523223",
"children":[
"Diagnosis"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f58a00",
"children":[
"The characteristic findings of ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heparin-induced thrombocytopenia",
"children":[
"HIT"
]
},
" and ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"heparin-induced thrombocytopenia with thrombosis",
"children":[
"HITT"
]
},
" are a platelet decrease >150,000/μL or >50% decrease from baseline in a patient taking heparin or a thromboembolic event 5 to 10 days after starting heparin."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e38ab7",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Patients with recent past exposure to heparin may experience the onset of HIT more rapidly after re-exposure to heparin."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"440866",
"children":[
"The 4T scoring algorithm is used to stratify the likelihood of HIT."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s23_2",
"title":{
"__html":"Testing"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"fa6a5a",
"children":[
"Testing"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"fa2bd0",
"children":[
"Diagnostic testing for HIT includes ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"enzyme-linked immunosorbent assay",
"children":[
"ELISA"
]
},
" for heparin/",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"platelet factor 4",
"children":[
"PF4"
]
},
" antibodies and the functional assays, of which the serotonin release assay is the gold standard."
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s23_3",
"title":{
"__html":"Treatment"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"4c4ac0",
"children":[
"Treatment"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"e865f6",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"alert",
"children":[
"Therapy is instituted before the results of diagnostic testing are returned if clinical suspicion is high (elevated 4T score). Heparin must be discontinued immediately."
]
},
" "
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"f788fa",
"children":[
"Use a nonheparin anticoagulant (e.g., argatroban, fondaparinux, bivalirudin, danaparoid, or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"direct oral anticoagulant",
"children":[
"DOAC"
]
},
") to stabilize the patient."
]
},
{
"type":"heading",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
"Don't Be Tricked"
]
},
{
"type":"list",
"class":"tricked",
"children":[
" ",
{
"type":"list-item",
"hlId":"ca5355",
"children":[
"For HIT or HITT, warfarin or ",
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"low-molecular-weight heparin",
"children":[
"LMWH"
]
},
" cannot be substituted for ",
{
"type":"no-wrap",
"children":[
{
"type":"abbreviation",
"title":"unfractionated heparin",
"children":[
"UFH"
]
},
"."
]
}
]
},
" "
]
}
]
},
{
"type":"section",
"id":"mk19_bb_hm_s23_4",
"title":{
"__html":"Test Yourself"
},
"titleNode":{
"type":"section-title",
"hlId":"7866cc",
"children":[
"Test Yourself"
]
},
"children":[
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"60bdbf",
"class":"test",
"children":[
"A 75-year-old man who has been hospitalized several times for ischemic heart disease is admitted with increasing chest pain. The morning after admission, he has a painful, cold left lower leg. The platelet count is 30,000/μL."
]
},
{
"type":"p",
"hlId":"843857",
"class":"test_answer",
"children":[
{
"type":"tag",
"tagName":"b",
"attrs":{
},
"children":[
"Answer:"
]
},
" ",
"For diagnosis, choose HITT. For management, stop heparin and begin argatroban."
]
}
]
}
]
